Business Case :A telecommunications company is experiencing customer attrition and needs to understand the factors driving churn to develop targeted retention strategies. With customer acquisition costs significantly higher than retention costs, reducing churn by even a few percentage points can substantially impact profitability.

Objective: Analyze customer demographics, service usage patterns, contract terms, and billing behaviors to identify high-risk customer segments and actionable insights that can inform:

Targeted retention campaigns
Product bundling strategies
Contract and pricing optimization
Customer service improvements
Expected Outcomes:

Identify key churn drivers and at-risk customer profiles
Quantify the revenue impact of churn
Develop data-driven retention strategies with measurable ROI
